title: Mick Farren & The Deviants Discography
description:
The leading agit-prop band was the Deviants, which were born as the British version of the Fugs, but soon developed an even more iconoclastic and unpredictable sound via
Ptooff, their masterpiece, Disposable, III and Mick Farren's solo album Mona: The Carnivorous Circus.

contains: 
(1967) Ptooff!
(1968) Disposable
(1969) The Deviants
(1970) Mona: The Carnivorous Circus
(1978) Vampires Stole My Lunch Money
